THE
Cabinet Lekgotla will not be discussing anything that has to do with the
removal of President Jacob Zuma.This
was a clear message by the Minister of Communications Mmamoloko Kubayi-Ngubane
while addressing the media on the first day of the cabinet meeting which
started on Wednesday. Cabinet
Lekgotla will sit at the Sefako Makgatho Presidential Guesthouse in Tshwane
