<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>“The
cabinet hasn’t received any communication from other political parties about
Zuma’s removal but the matter will not be part of the discussions in this
cabinet meeting,” she said. Cabinet
Lekgotla is a gathering of Ministers, Deputy Ministers, Director-Generals and
other government officials.The
three-day meeting will be led by President Zuma and Deputy President Cyril
Ramaphosa, who shared jokes during the first day about Zuma being the Mayor of
Nkandla.Kubayi-Ngubane
said during the Lekgotla, the cabinet will be discussing the economy and how
they can grow it.She
said this meeting will also be part of the preparations for the State of the
Nation Address [SoNA] and the upcoming budget speech.Aside
from economic growth, Minister Kubayi-Ngubane said cabinet would also be
discussing job creation in Mzansi.“Creating
jobs is part of our work as government and the cabinet,” she said.She
said matters around higher education will also take priority at the Lekgotla.She
said more details will be outlined in the SoNA about how they going to move
forward in putting everything in motion.Kubayi-Ngubane
said on Friday they will be a joint meeting with the premiers and local
government officials.“As
part of ensuring that our work as government goes across to the national,
provincial and local government, we will all be meeting in a joint meeting,”
she said.